%section
  %h2 Features
  %ol
    %li
      %p
        You host your own files. This means that you have full ownership and control over what happens to them, if our datacenter explodes into a billion tiny little pieces, you will still have your files. You can set up your own private hosting using services like:
        = succeed "," do
          %a{:href => "http://aws.amazon.com/s3/", :title => "Amazon Simple Storage Service (Amazon S3)"} Amazon S3
        = succeed "," do
          %a{:href => "http://www.rackspace.com/cloud/cloud_hosting_products/files/", :title => "Cloud Files - Unlimited Online Storage &amp; Data Storage Services"} CloudFiles
        SFTP, or FTP.
    %li
      %p
        You customize your own interface using SiteScripts. This means that if you want a special feature in your web interface (say for example a simple slideshow feature to show off your images at work or class), you have full freedom to build the feature using
        %a{:href => "http://www.liquidmarkup.org/", :title => "Liquid Templating language"} liquid templates
        and JavaScript.
    %li.last
      %p
        You use community-built features. There is somewhat of an 'app store' (which is 100% free of course) where you can take advantage of the cool features that other users have written using the
        %a{:href => "#"} SiteScripts
        framework. These features will be curated and approved by the people who run STSH.ME.
